================ Prompt Escape Sequences  ================
Code	Meaning				Example Output
\u	Username			rod
\h	Hostname (short)		Mac-Pro
\H	Hostname (full)			Mac-Pro.local
\w	Current working dir (full path)	/Users/rod
\W	Current dir (basename only)	rod
\t	Current time (HH:MM:SS)		14:32:18
\T	Current time (12-hr format)	02:32:18
\d	Date				Mon Apr 08
\n	Newline	
\!	Command history number		512
\#	Command number (this session)	42
\$	$ for normal user, # for root	$ or #
\[	Start of non-printing characters (like color)	
\]	End of non-printing characters	

#export PS1="\[\e[1;32m\]\u@\h \[\e[1;34m\]\w\[\e[0m\] $ "
================ Prompt Escape Sequences  ================

================ CHMOD Octal reference  ================

" Octal | Binary | File Mode
" ------|--------|-----------
"   0   |  000   |   ---
"   1   |  001   |   --x
"   2   |  010   |   -w-
"   3   |  011   |   -wx
"   4   |  100   |   r--
"   5   |  101   |   r-x
"   6   |  110   |   rw-
"   7   |  111   |   rwx

" Examples:
" chmod 755 file.txt > rwxr-xr-x
" chmod 777 file.txt → rwxrwxrwx
" chmod 644 file.txt → rw-r--r--
" chmod 600 secrets  → rw-------

================ CHMOD Octal reference  ================

